Introducing scalar and vector potentials, ϕ and A the unknowns in Maxwell‘s equations will be reduced from six (three components of E and B) to four (ϕ and three components of A). In the study of electromagnetism [18], especially when potentials are introduced two identities are important, i.e., the curl of the gradient of any scalar field is zero (∇ × ∇ϕ = 0), and the divergence of the curl of any vector field is zero (∇·∇ × A = 0). Hence after some manipulations and substitution, we get the following relationships:10\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
